						               													<description>Block Arena, an abstract game for 2 players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In Block Arena each player controls 4 blocks and 1 meeple. Players move their blocks and meeples, with the aim of making their own meeple reach the opposite side of the board.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A match lasts about 15 minutes.&amp;#10;The game is very simple to learn, but hard to master, and it has a very good amount of replayability.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;___________________________________________________________________________________&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Block Arena was designed and created by Marco Boschiero between May and June 2018, in Rome.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Now Block Arena is also on Tabletop Simulator, thanks to Fernando Fiorenzano and Michele Cristofani!&amp;#10;https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=2919125856&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Here's the Facebook page where you can find informations about the game and share comments and playtests!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Marco.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;___________________________________________________________________________________&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Thanks to all the people that made this possible, especially playtesters, other game designers and friends.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A special thanks to:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;- Ignazio Panades, that gave a huge contribution for the game development;&amp;#10;- Marco, that played with me the first correspondence Block Arena match in history;&amp;#10;- Claudia Minozzi, Stefano and all the other boardgames course students, that gave me the first impressions of the game and encouraged me to go on with the project;&amp;#10;- Fernando Fiorenzano for bringing it here on TTS!&amp;#10;- Michele Cristofani for working at the very first version of it on TTS;&amp;#10;- my family, the best playtesters ever!&amp;#10;- all the people that made this possible!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
